The static keyword in Java is used for memory management mainly. We can apply static keyword with variables, methods, blocks and nested classes. The static keyword belongs to the class than an instance of the class.

The static can be:

1. Variable (also known as a class variable)
2. Method (also known as a class method)
3. Block
4. Nested class

Static method
- static method belongs to a class not to a object
- static method can be accessed directly by class name and does not need any object
- it can access only static data
- it can call only static method
- it cannot refer to this or super keyword